If you tell everyone about the stock
deal, it will blow up in your face.

756
01:02:05,751 --> 01:02:07,778
Who will you tell next? Michael?

757
01:02:07,836 --> 01:02:11,370
He came down here to find investors
for that moronic club of his.

758
01:02:11,423 --> 01:02:14,708
- He came down for Alex's funeral.
- Maybe.

759
01:02:16,178 --> 01:02:19,498
You are in no condition
to discuss this now.

760
01:02:19,807 --> 01:02:21,880
You can't change people's lives!

761
01:02:21,975 --> 01:02:25,758
Who do you think you are,
John Beresford Tipton?

762
01:02:26,355 --> 01:02:28,097
I'm going to sleep.

763
01:02:30,943 --> 01:02:34,097
How can you go to sleep?
I'm not even tired.

764
01:03:04,184 --> 01:03:07,800
Some say suicide is the ultimate
act of self-absorption.

765
01:03:07,855 --> 01:03:10,806
Alex didn't commit suicide.
It was an accident.

766
01:03:10,899 --> 01:03:14,883
That's right, he was shaving.
Alex had hairy wrists.

767
01:03:16,405 --> 01:03:19,060
Masturbation's the ultimate
act of self-absorption.

768
01:03:19,158 --> 01:03:20,935
You jerk off?

769
01:03:21,201 --> 01:03:23,193
Does a bear have fleas?

770
01:03:23,245 --> 01:03:25,603
No, does a bear shit in the woods?

771
01:03:25,706 --> 01:03:26,985
Does a bear jerk off?

772
01:03:27,082 --> 01:03:29,489
I shit in the woods,
but I can't jerk off.

773
01:03:29,585 --> 01:03:31,346
We're trying to avoid
dealing with Alex.

774
01:03:31,378 --> 01:03:33,618
Every time it comes up,
someone changes the subject.

775
01:03:33,630 --> 01:03:35,538
It's a dead subject.

776
01:03:35,591 --> 01:03:37,997
I get real tired of these jokes.

777
01:03:38,052 --> 01:03:40,956
What are we afraid of?
To show our emotions?

778
01:03:41,013 --> 01:03:43,336
Are we mad at him for
leaving no explanations?

779
01:03:43,432 --> 01:03:47,167
I could say something funny
about that. But I won't.

780
01:03:47,227 --> 01:03:49,503
Great, they got here early.

781
01:03:55,444 --> 01:03:56,844
Thanks, Toby. I appreciate it.

782
01:03:56,904 --> 01:04:00,140
Yes, sir, Mr. Cooper.
It was my pleasure.

783
01:04:02,743 --> 01:04:05,979
Yes, sir, Mr. Cooper. Sir.

784
01:04:06,038 --> 01:04:08,480
Give me a break, that's my name.

785
01:04:08,791 --> 01:04:10,449
Mr. Weber.

786
01:05:12,521 --> 01:05:14,678
So you just fell asleep?

787
01:05:14,773 --> 01:05:17,180
That's what I just said, didn't I?

788
01:05:17,276 --> 01:05:19,385
About five times.

789
01:05:19,903 --> 01:05:23,519
I didn't know him in the
biblical sense. Is that clear?

790
01:05:23,574 --> 01:05:25,019
I don't know why you're touchy.

791
01:05:25,075 --> 01:05:27,315
I don't know why you're curious.

792
01:05:30,456 --> 01:05:32,150
These feel great.

793
01:05:33,167 --> 01:05:36,071
I'm never taking these off.
I will sleep in them.

794
01:05:36,170 --> 01:05:39,205
Which doesn't mean he'll
have sex with them.

795
01:05:40,215 --> 01:05:43,369
Is there any salt
and pepper, please?

796
01:05:55,022 --> 01:05:59,220
What do you think about this
latest brainstorm of Michael's?

797
01:06:02,446 --> 01:06:06,311
I'm not sure I want to be part
owner of a jet-set greasy spoon.

798
01:06:07,868 --> 01:06:10,476
Think we could stall
him for a while?

799
01:06:14,291 --> 01:06:15,654
What is that?

800
01:06:15,709 --> 01:06:18,198
Nick wanted to take a
look at the property.

801
01:06:18,253 --> 01:06:21,324
He'll be back before
the game starts.

802
01:06:26,970 --> 01:06:28,415
Thanks.

803
01:06:58,210 --> 01:07:00,118
Are we the first ones up?

804
01:07:06,969 --> 01:07:10,004
You remember. Alex used
to call me Sam the Sham.

805
01:07:10,055 --> 01:07:11,666
Don't say that. It was real.

806
01:07:11,724 --> 01:07:16,336
I stood with thousands of people
listening to you. You moved them.

807
01:07:16,395 --> 01:07:19,264
Now I reach millions
of people every week.

808
01:07:19,314 --> 01:07:21,174
Hell, it's just garbage.

809
01:07:21,275 --> 01:07:23,681
That's not true. You
entertain people.

810
01:07:23,777 --> 01:07:26,184
God knows, we need that now.

811
01:07:26,739 --> 01:07:27,769
I try.

812
01:07:27,823 --> 01:07:31,724
I try once every show to put
something of value in there.

813
01:07:31,785 --> 01:07:33,563
- But I don't know.
- You do.

814
01:07:33,620 --> 01:07:34,686
I can see it.

815
01:07:35,664 --> 01:07:38,735
I feel my kids have gotten
something from J.T. Lancer.

816
01:07:38,751 --> 01:07:39,982
Really?

817
01:07:42,337 --> 01:07:43,700
Kids.

818
01:07:44,715 --> 01:07:47,038
There you go. You've
done something.

819
01:07:47,134 --> 01:07:50,584
You and Richard have built
something for yourselves.

820
01:07:52,056 --> 01:07:54,544
You know the secret of Richard?

821
01:07:56,727 --> 01:07:58,718
Remember my father?

822
01:08:00,064 --> 01:08:02,837
I didn't want that to happen to me.

823
01:08:02,900 --> 01:08:06,303
Richard looked like all that had
been missing in my childhood.

824
01:08:06,445 --> 01:08:09,848
A man like that could build a
stable environment for children.

825
01:08:09,907 --> 01:08:11,435
And he did.

826
01:08:11,658 --> 01:08:13,732
It's just that now...

827
01:08:19,416 --> 01:08:20,779
What?

828
01:08:21,877 --> 01:08:23,737
Well, you know.

829
01:08:25,172 --> 01:08:26,285
Tell me.

830
01:08:28,092 --> 01:08:30,830
Well, it's not like talking to you.

831
01:08:32,888 --> 01:08:35,413
All my life, deep inside...

832
01:08:35,891 --> 01:08:38,926
I felt there was something
I wanted to express...

833
01:08:38,977 --> 01:08:42,297
but always felt, I
don't know, stymied.

834
01:08:43,774 --> 01:08:47,259
I'm proud of what I did. I'm doing
a good job of raising my sons.

835
01:08:47,319 --> 01:08:52,098
If it meant giving up my
writing, that's the way it goes.

836
01:08:53,784 --> 01:08:56,819
- You don't remember my writing.
- Sure I do.

837
01:08:56,870 --> 01:08:59,822
It's just poems and short stories.

838
01:09:01,083 --> 01:09:03,359
I didn't show it to many people.

839
01:09:05,170 --> 01:09:07,908
Why talk about it?
I made my decision.

840
01:09:07,965 --> 01:09:10,039
My children come first.

841
01:09:10,968 --> 01:09:14,204
It's just that now it
leaves kind of a...

842
01:09:15,180 --> 01:09:17,587
I don't know, a space.

843
01:09:18,559 --> 01:09:20,882
And all of Richard's...

844
01:09:20,936 --> 01:09:25,264
country clubs and home
improvements and business deals...

845
01:09:26,316 --> 01:09:29,007
are pretty superficial stuff.

846
01:09:30,279 --> 01:09:33,563
I'm not complaining.
Well, maybe I am.

847
01:09:33,991 --> 01:09:35,305
Sorry.

848
01:09:36,201 --> 01:09:37,730
It's just...

849
01:09:37,786 --> 01:09:39,445
being with you...

850
01:09:40,706 --> 01:09:42,780
opens me up somehow.

851
01:09:45,002 --> 01:09:46,530
Forgive me?

852
01:09:59,266 --> 01:10:02,301
<i>Hail to the conquering heroes.
Come on, the game's starting!</i>

853
01:10:02,352 --> 01:10:04,675
You don't want to
miss any of the Blue.

854
01:10:04,772 --> 01:10:06,549
Yes, you do, all right.

855
01:10:07,900 --> 01:10:10,591
<i>And you were ready to write
this one off at 10-0.</i>

856
01:10:10,611 --> 01:10:14,559
<i>- I didn't say anything about that.
- I saw that smile.</i>

857
01:10:15,491 --> 01:10:17,600
That pass, I can't believe it.

858
01:10:17,785 --> 01:10:19,064
Go, go, go!

859
01:10:27,002 --> 01:10:28,447
A flag? What?

860
01:10:29,254 --> 01:10:31,079
What are they calling that?

861
01:10:31,131 --> 01:10:32,612
- What is that?
- Clipping.

862
01:10:32,716 --> 01:10:34,292
That was a clean hit.

863
01:10:34,343 --> 01:10:37,295
- He clipped him.
- What are you talking about?!

864
01:10:37,388 --> 01:10:40,542
<i>Clipping. Called against Michigan.</i>

865
01:10:42,851 --> 01:10:44,925
Sorry, Chloe.

866
01:10:45,979 --> 01:10:48,421
Come on, Blue, you're not supposed
to fold till the fourth quarter.

867
01:10:48,482 --> 01:10:50,888
Don't heckle Bo. He's
got enough pressure.

868
01:10:51,777 --> 01:10:55,144
Where is Nick? I can't
believe he's missing this.

869
01:10:55,739 --> 01:10:58,691
Teach them the basics, Bo.
Ugliest helmets in the world.

870
01:11:02,955 --> 01:11:04,946
I don't know.

871
01:11:05,457 --> 01:11:09,737
Sometimes I wonder if I was
sick of being a good girl.

872
01:11:10,045 --> 01:11:12,950
I could be counted on
to do the right thing.

873
01:11:13,048 --> 01:11:15,573
It's a disgusting curse.

874
01:11:15,676 --> 01:11:18,793
Probably thought Alex could
touch that part of me...

875
01:11:18,887 --> 01:11:21,839
that was unpredictable and magic.

876
01:11:22,099 --> 01:11:24,256
The part I was always afraid of.

877
01:11:24,393 --> 01:11:26,835
Who knows if it's even there?

878
01:11:27,896 --> 01:11:30,469
When it was over, everything
went back to how it was before.

879
01:11:30,566 --> 01:11:33,517
That's what we all agreed.
That's what we all said.

880
01:11:33,819 --> 01:11:38,515
I was sorry everyone knew, but that
was as much my fault as anything.

881
01:11:38,615 --> 01:11:40,393
Of course...

882
01:11:40,492 --> 01:11:43,100
things weren't really the same.

883
01:11:43,746 --> 01:11:46,234
Alex withdrew from me then.

884
01:11:46,665 --> 01:11:49,154
I was probably different with him.

885
01:11:49,585 --> 01:11:52,276
We never wanted Harold
to think that...

886
01:11:53,797 --> 01:11:55,326
You can imagine.

887
01:11:57,634 --> 01:12:02,710
So we finally consummated
this ancient lurking passion.

888
01:12:02,931 --> 01:12:06,465
All it had done was put up
a wall in our friendship.

889
01:12:11,857 --> 01:12:13,136
What?

890
01:12:13,192 --> 01:12:15,016
He's not passing!

891
01:12:17,571 --> 01:12:20,855
Nobody in the area.
Who was he passing to?

892
01:12:20,949 --> 01:12:23,438
I'm sure you're happy.
He threw it right to you!

893
01:12:23,535 --> 01:12:25,016
Idiot!

894
01:12:26,038 --> 01:12:30,366
They're flying up a new quarterback
from Texas or something.

895
01:12:32,127 --> 01:12:33,987
What? I didn't throw the ball.

896
01:12:34,046 --> 01:12:36,285
So what am I, chopped liver?

897
01:12:36,340 --> 01:12:38,579
- What are you talking about?
- You know.

898
01:12:38,634 --> 01:12:40,873
- No, I don't.
- You know.

899
01:12:42,638 --> 01:12:44,415
You asked Sam.

900
01:12:44,515 --> 01:12:46,458
What is this, published somewhere?

901
01:12:46,517 --> 01:12:49,208
You know we can do it.
We've done it.

902
01:12:49,853 --> 01:12:53,257
Remember the march on Washington?
Armies of the night?

903
01:12:53,315 --> 01:12:55,057
I remember.

904
01:12:55,901 --> 01:12:57,726
I thought you'd be grateful.

905
01:12:57,778 --> 01:13:01,014
- You're sweeping me off my feet.
- I thought you wanted a kid.

906
01:13:02,199 --> 01:13:03,679
Thank you, Michael.

907
01:13:04,410 --> 01:13:06,318
This is a big decision.

908
01:13:06,412 --> 01:13:09,019
I'll get back to you
in the third quarter.

909
01:14:05,846 --> 01:14:10,091
Look at this! This could be us!
The next generation.

910
01:14:10,184 --> 01:14:12,460
It could be. Think about it.

911
01:14:12,519 --> 01:14:13,882
Think!

912
01:14:32,289 --> 01:14:33,734
Shit.

913
01:14:40,672 --> 01:14:42,450
- How you doing, Harold?
- Not bad.

914
01:14:42,508 --> 01:14:45,163
This guy claims to be
a guest. That true?

915
01:14:45,260 --> 01:14:46,623
Depends. What'd he do?

916
01:14:46,678 --> 01:14:49,120
- For one, he ran a red light.
- No, I didn't.

917
01:14:49,181 --> 01:14:52,501
- He became verbally abusive.
- You got etiquette laws here?

918
01:14:52,559 --> 01:14:54,218
25 bucks he's hitting me for!

919
01:14:54,269 --> 01:14:59,345
He could be one of them Yankee
drug dealers we sometimes get...

920
01:14:59,441 --> 01:15:01,433
passing through on
their way to Florida.

921
01:15:01,527 --> 01:15:04,300
This is my lawyer.
I don't have to take this.

922
01:15:04,363 --> 01:15:06,639
It's true, officer. Do
you have probable cause?

923
01:15:06,865 --> 01:15:09,354
Excuse me, aren't you J.T. Lancer?

924
01:15:10,160 --> 01:15:11,771
Yes, sir, Officer.

925
01:15:12,955 --> 01:15:16,239
I'll be. What's that
make you, Perry Mason?

926
01:15:17,042 --> 01:15:19,864
You know, Pete. He does
look suspicious to me too.

927
01:15:19,962 --> 01:15:23,079
Let's take him out back and
kick the shit out of him.

928
01:15:23,549 --> 01:15:26,536
Must be quick. The second
half of the game's starting.

929
01:15:32,683 --> 01:15:35,504
I'd be willing to drop
this whole thing...

930
01:15:35,602 --> 01:15:38,128
if you could persuade
Mr. Lancer into showing us...

931
01:15:38,230 --> 01:15:41,003
how he hops into
that sports car on TV.

932
01:15:41,734 --> 01:15:43,760
I'd really appreciate it.

933
01:15:43,861 --> 01:15:46,599
I watch that show every week
and I've always wondered.

934
01:15:46,864 --> 01:15:50,018
Myself, I always have to
open the damn car door.

935
01:15:50,159 --> 01:15:51,936
You have a hard top.

936
01:15:52,619 --> 01:15:53,982
Don't do it.

937
01:16:00,044 --> 01:16:01,702
Go for it.

938
01:16:15,059 --> 01:16:16,504
I don't believe this.

939
01:16:21,482 --> 01:16:23,010
Damn it!

940
01:16:27,029 --> 01:16:28,806
It's not that bad, guys!

941
01:16:28,864 --> 01:16:30,689
Don't talk. Don't try to talk.

942
01:16:30,783 --> 01:16:32,525
Make sure you keep his arm up.

943
01:16:32,576 --> 01:16:34,852
Am I going to need a tetanus shot?

944
01:16:36,330 --> 01:16:39,531
- You won't amputate, will you?
- I got to see.

945
01:16:39,625 --> 01:16:40,987
What about my career?

946
01:16:41,210 --> 01:16:44,613
I am sorry. I thought
they could do that stuff.

947
01:16:44,671 --> 01:16:45,903
It's not your fault.

948
01:16:46,715 --> 01:16:49,453
- Enjoy that second half, now.
- Will do.

949
01:16:52,471 --> 01:16:55,921
Since when did you get
so friendly with cops?

950
01:17:02,356 --> 01:17:04,465
You know, you're fucking stupid.

951
01:17:05,776 --> 01:17:07,221
Stupid!

952
01:17:07,653 --> 01:17:11,352
That cop has twice kept this
house from being ripped off.

953
01:17:11,448 --> 01:17:13,641
Happens to be a hell of a guy.

954
01:17:14,159 --> 01:17:15,735
And you...

955
01:17:18,872 --> 01:17:20,982
Come on, what is it?

956
01:17:27,297 --> 01:17:29,075
What is it with you?

957
01:17:30,300 --> 01:17:34,498
Is jail another experience to try?
See what it's like?

958
01:17:38,475 --> 01:17:40,335
You know, I live here.

959
01:17:41,270 --> 01:17:44,921
This place means something
to me. I'm dug in.

960
01:17:45,441 --> 01:17:47,633
I don't need this shit.

961
01:17:58,954 --> 01:18:01,147
You know, I really can do it.

962
01:18:01,206 --> 01:18:04,407
It's these damn running shoes.
They practically kill me.

963
01:18:04,543 --> 01:18:06,154
We know you can.

964
01:18:06,587 --> 01:18:09,538
Being a private eye
is dangerous work.

965
01:18:11,467 --> 01:18:14,122
I got to get back
to the game, coach.

966
01:18:14,636 --> 01:18:16,035
Walk.

967
01:18:17,973 --> 01:18:20,379
We're deep in the third quarter.

968
01:18:21,226 --> 01:18:23,502
Just testing. A little joke.

969
01:18:26,523 --> 01:18:30,591
Michael has graciously agreed
to act as stud for me.

970
01:18:30,819 --> 01:18:32,846
A repeat performance.

971
01:18:32,905 --> 01:18:34,932
He didn't say that, did he?

972
01:18:34,990 --> 01:18:37,681
Well, it's almost that romantic.

973
01:18:37,785 --> 01:18:39,977
What are you going to do?

974
01:18:44,249 --> 01:18:48,068
I can't do it with him. Too
much history, it's not right.

975
01:18:48,128 --> 01:18:52,492
I can't believe this. I'm just
deciding this as we speak.

976
01:18:53,550 --> 01:18:56,039
It's not going to
happen this weekend.

977
01:18:57,304 --> 01:19:00,920
Maybe it's a sign from God
that I should reconsider.

978
01:19:01,058 --> 01:19:03,167
Too bad I'm an atheist.

979
01:19:07,523 --> 01:19:09,680
- Like what?
- Say anything.

980
01:19:09,942 --> 01:19:12,099
Tell us about your past.

981
01:19:12,236 --> 01:19:14,808
- I lived with Alex.
- Before that.

982
01:19:14,905 --> 01:19:16,480
Before that.

983
01:19:16,573 --> 01:19:17,936
Randy.

984
01:19:21,161 --> 01:19:25,655
I don't like talking about my
past as much as you guys do.

985
01:19:27,543 --> 01:19:29,534
Okay, I'll buy that.

986
01:19:30,629 --> 01:19:34,530
Can you tell us
something about Alex?

987
01:19:36,093 --> 01:19:38,001
Well, he was cute.

988
01:19:39,888 --> 01:19:45,046
He said we made a good couple because I
had no expectations and he had too many.

989
01:19:49,106 --> 01:19:51,714
<i>He believed in reincarnation.</i>

990
01:19:54,236 --> 01:19:56,345
<i>He never ate meat.</i>

991
01:19:56,405 --> 01:20:00,899
<i>He said he was afraid he would
come back someday as a steak.</i>

992
01:20:04,538 --> 01:20:08,818
<i>He said he should have accepted
that Rutledge fellowship.</i>

993
01:20:16,050 --> 01:20:17,578
<i>What's the matter, Nick?</i>

994
01:20:21,805 --> 01:20:24,675
Two, three, four.

995
01:20:45,287 --> 01:20:50,612
The biggest mistake I made was not
trying harder to steal you from Nick.

996
01:20:50,834 --> 01:20:53,442
You know I always
wanted you to try.

997
01:20:55,923 --> 01:20:57,617
I never got that feeling.

998
01:20:57,716 --> 01:21:00,123
I guess you weren't
paying attention.

999
01:21:03,680 --> 01:21:06,418
It's a little late now, isn't it?

1000
01:21:06,809 --> 01:21:08,088
Is it?

1001
01:21:09,895 --> 01:21:11,554
What are you saying?

1002
01:21:11,605 --> 01:21:12,920
I think you know.

1003
01:21:13,524 --> 01:21:15,965
I think you've known
this whole weekend.

1004
01:21:16,235 --> 01:21:18,427
Wait, you mean you and Richard...?

1005
01:21:18,612 --> 01:21:21,599
See? You've always
been able to read me.

1006
01:21:21,782 --> 01:21:24,473
You know my life with
Richard isn't working.

1007
01:21:25,077 --> 01:21:28,064
Well, I knew you two
weren't exactly...

1008
01:21:28,122 --> 01:21:29,484
But I didn't think-

1009
01:21:29,540 --> 01:21:31,364
I'm going to leave him.

1010
01:21:32,251 --> 01:21:34,739
Let's get the Wonton
Express rolling.

1011
01:21:35,295 --> 01:21:37,155
You want to come along?

1012
01:21:37,214 --> 01:21:38,908
No, you go ahead.

1013
01:21:40,884 --> 01:21:42,662
I'll be right here.

1014
01:21:44,513 --> 01:21:46,836
Just climb in there regular, okay?

1015
01:22:07,286 --> 01:22:09,028
Listen to those guys.

1016
01:22:09,079 --> 01:22:10,655
Goddamn!

1017
01:22:11,957 --> 01:22:14,565
Remember the night
we saw them in Cobo?

1018
01:22:16,795 --> 01:22:18,537
No, you probably don't.

1019
01:22:18,922 --> 01:22:21,660
You were hallucinating
pretty bad that night.

1020
01:22:25,471 --> 01:22:27,710
We didn't even have any drugs.

1021
01:22:28,515 --> 01:22:32,499
Have you noticed anything
unusual about this weekend?

1022
01:22:32,644 --> 01:22:34,588
Other than Alex dying?

1023
01:22:34,688 --> 01:22:38,138
I've been getting some
pretty weird propositions.

1024
01:22:39,651 --> 01:22:42,722
I don't think I could live
down here all the time.

1025
01:22:45,741 --> 01:22:48,858
Last year I went to Hawaii
with my friend Reena.

1026
01:22:48,911 --> 01:22:53,025
We ate at a Chinese restaurant.
When they brought the fortune cookies...

1027
01:22:53,082 --> 01:22:55,191
hers said, "You'll never
amount to anything."

1028
01:22:55,250 --> 01:22:56,909
I don't believe it.

1029
01:23:02,132 --> 01:23:04,574
"Friendship is the
bread of life..."

1030
01:23:04,635 --> 01:23:06,792
Wait a minute!
"...but money is the honey."

1031
01:23:06,929 --> 01:23:08,540
It doesn't say that.

1032
01:23:08,597 --> 01:23:10,671
- You're kidding.
- That's great!

1033
01:23:10,766 --> 01:23:13,539
Even fortune cookies
are getting cynical!

1034
01:23:13,602 --> 01:23:15,047
Cynical? It's pragmatic.

1035
01:23:15,104 --> 01:23:17,343
I think it's touching.

1036
01:24:00,983 --> 01:24:04,516
There's nothing I'd rather do
right now than make love to you.

1037
01:24:08,574 --> 01:24:10,149
When it's over...

1038
01:24:10,242 --> 01:24:12,233
come into my life.

1039
01:24:12,870 --> 01:24:16,818
You and your kids come out
to L.A., move into my house.

1040
01:24:17,124 --> 01:24:20,989
There's plenty of room.
It's lovely, it's great.

1041
01:24:22,880 --> 01:24:24,538
I can't do that.

1042
01:24:26,425 --> 01:24:28,701
It has to do with Robin.

1043
01:24:29,011 --> 01:24:33,078
No, it's not that. My
marriage is completely over.

1044
01:24:33,432 --> 01:24:37,843
When Robin and I broke up,
I had a million good reasons.

1045
01:24:37,895 --> 01:24:41,962
A million things that were
wrong with her, wrong with us.

1046
01:24:42,357 --> 01:24:44,764
When I think back on it now...

1047
01:24:45,069 --> 01:24:49,562
and see my daughter with her new
father, I realize what broke us up.

1048
01:24:49,656 --> 01:24:52,976
What really did it, and I
hate to admit it, even now.

1049
01:24:53,786 --> 01:24:56,025
What did it was...

1050
01:24:58,123 --> 01:24:59,568
boredom.

1051
01:25:00,209 --> 01:25:02,318
I couldn't stick with it.

1052
01:25:05,631 --> 01:25:08,536
I'd hate to see you
make that same mistake.

1053
01:25:11,887 --> 01:25:14,376
You're a much better
person than that.

1054
01:25:15,599 --> 01:25:17,922
Don't give me that shit!

1055
01:25:18,143 --> 01:25:21,261
For 15 years, you've acted like
I'm the one you really wanted.

1056
01:25:21,313 --> 01:25:23,221
You made sure everyone knew.

1057
01:25:23,273 --> 01:25:25,632
And now I come down here-

1058
01:25:36,036 --> 01:25:38,145
Don't be mad at him, honey.

1059
01:25:40,541 --> 01:25:42,401
Well, it's called an anus.

1060
01:25:43,210 --> 01:25:47,538
I'm sure it is boring to hear it
20 times, but just ignore him.

1061
01:25:48,048 --> 01:25:49,624
All right.

1062
01:25:50,342 --> 01:25:52,334
Yes. Just a minute.

1063
01:25:52,386 --> 01:25:53,997
She's right here.

1064
01:25:54,638 --> 01:25:56,297
No, just hold on.

1065
01:26:00,185 --> 01:26:03,386
Hello, muffin. How are you?

1066
01:26:03,731 --> 01:26:06,137
You got it? Great!

1067
01:26:06,191 --> 01:26:07,720
You did?

1068
01:26:07,776 --> 01:26:13,101
When I saw it, I said I have one friend
in the world who'd appreciate it.

1069
01:26:13,240 --> 01:26:15,682
That's going to be
our little secret.

1070
01:26:21,290 --> 01:26:24,195
As soon as your mommy
and daddy say you can.

1071
01:26:24,251 --> 01:26:26,740
When do you get off from school?

1072
01:26:38,557 --> 01:26:40,714
So what would that have meant?

1073
01:26:40,809 --> 01:26:44,046
What do you mean? It
would've told us something.

1074
01:26:44,229 --> 01:26:45,710
What are you talking about?

1075
01:26:45,814 --> 01:26:48,422
Meg is pissed off because
Alex didn't leave a note.

1076
01:26:48,525 --> 01:26:51,395
- Could he summed it up in a note?
- Maybe a long note.

1077
01:26:51,779 --> 01:26:55,063
I can sum up people's
lives in 32 paragraphs.

1078
01:26:55,115 --> 01:26:58,352
I did a rock band in a page and
a half and they had 2 drummers.

1079
01:26:59,161 --> 01:27:01,567
Do you think this is funny?

1080
01:27:02,289 --> 01:27:06,617
One of our best friends kills
himself and we don't know why.

1081
01:27:07,211 --> 01:27:11,574
No one knows why anyone does anything.
Why did I choose these socks today?

1082
01:27:12,299 --> 01:27:15,868
There's a great equation:
Your socks, Alex's death.

1083
01:27:16,887 --> 01:27:18,665
They're pretty sad socks.

1084
01:27:18,764 --> 01:27:22,048
I believe that everybody
does everything to get laid.

1085
01:27:22,267 --> 01:27:23,843
Who said that? Freud?

1086
01:27:23,894 --> 01:27:25,292
No, I did.

1087
01:27:26,063 --> 01:27:30,130
All I'm saying is how could we
let Alex slip away like that?

1088
01:27:30,192 --> 01:27:32,432
Maybe he let us slip away.
I never heard from him.

1089
01:27:32,528 --> 01:27:35,563
- Did he hear from you?
- I tried. He resisted.

1090
01:27:35,656 --> 01:27:37,054
It's true.

1091
01:27:37,116 --> 01:27:40,566
We saw him a lot.
But he didn't tell us much.

1092
01:27:40,661 --> 01:27:42,320
Not me anyway.

1093
01:27:42,413 --> 01:27:44,522
I can't speak for Sarah.

1094
01:27:44,707 --> 01:27:47,658
I knew he was unhappy.
That doesn't tell you much.

1095
01:27:47,751 --> 01:27:50,573
I had no idea how bad it was.

1096
01:27:50,754 --> 01:27:53,243
I think he wanted to
cut off from us...

1097
01:27:53,298 --> 01:27:55,787
because he was so unhappy
with where he was at.

1098
01:27:56,093 --> 01:27:58,701
Is that true, Chloe?
Did you feel that?

1099
01:27:58,929 --> 01:28:02,249
I don't know. We had
some good times.

1100
01:28:02,850 --> 01:28:07,877
I haven't met many happy people
in my life. How do they act?

1101
01:28:08,605 --> 01:28:10,632
I'm sitting here and I realize...

1102
01:28:11,191 --> 01:28:13,847
I don't know what he
did for the last 5 years.

1103
01:28:14,653 --> 01:28:17,344
I remember he left that
caseworker job in Boston.

1104
01:28:17,448 --> 01:28:19,771
That was, what, '78 or so?

1105
01:28:20,242 --> 01:28:22,731
I don't know why he was doing that.

1106
01:28:22,786 --> 01:28:26,651
He was a scientific genius.
Why was he doing welfare work?

1107
01:28:26,707 --> 01:28:28,667
Then the construction job.
What was that for?

1108
01:28:28,959 --> 01:28:30,737
He didn't know what to do.

1109
01:28:31,253 --> 01:28:32,995
I can relate to that.

1110
01:28:34,048 --> 01:28:37,451
If you'd been in touch with him,
you could've saved his life?

1111
01:28:37,676 --> 01:28:41,625
You have that effect on people?
Keep them all jolly, do you?

1112
01:28:43,140 --> 01:28:45,416
Wise up, folks. We're
alone out there.

1113
01:28:45,476 --> 01:28:48,546
And tomorrow we're
going out there again.

1114
01:28:48,771 --> 01:28:53,134
<i>It was straight of him not to cook
up a Reader's Digest condensation...</i>

1115
01:28:53,192 --> 01:28:55,717
of his screwed up life
for our entertainment.

1116
01:28:55,819 --> 01:29:00,099
I am sick of people selling
their psyches for attention.

1117
01:29:00,199 --> 01:29:02,107
He was classier than that.

1118
01:29:02,159 --> 01:29:05,028
It was a real classy act
he pulled in the bathtub.

1119
01:29:05,371 --> 01:29:09,817
For some people it isn't a question
of why kill yourself, but why not.

1120
01:29:10,667 --> 01:29:15,364
Give me a break. Spare us the
tragic existential pose.

1121
01:29:15,422 --> 01:29:17,698
Didn't mean to get into your area.

1122
01:29:17,758 --> 01:29:21,078
Come on now, guys. We're
all friends here.

1123
01:29:21,887 --> 01:29:23,332
This is a well-known dynamic.

1124
01:29:23,389 --> 01:29:25,139
I've seen it a million times.
Some people...

1125
01:29:25,140 --> 01:29:29,208
ease the pain of separation by
denigrating their relationship.

1126
01:29:30,229 --> 01:29:32,468
You're so deep.

1127
01:29:33,607 --> 01:29:35,716
I think Michael's right.

1128
01:29:35,776 --> 01:29:39,096
I feel shitty about 10
different ways tonight.

1129
01:29:39,154 --> 01:29:40,932
I don't want to let any of this go.

1130
01:29:41,156 --> 01:29:45,650
That's healthy. The only way to avoid
pain is to pretend you don't care.

1131
01:29:45,703 --> 01:29:47,942
I know. I've left more
places than you'll ever go.

1132
01:29:47,996 --> 01:29:49,739
Give him your pose line, Sam.

1133
01:29:49,790 --> 01:29:52,446
There's the existential man for you.
You're one tough cookie.

1134
01:29:52,501 --> 01:29:53,899
I could say you're one...

1135
01:29:54,002 --> 01:29:57,821
cold, manipulative guy
and it wouldn't bother you.

1136
01:29:58,215 --> 01:30:00,040
I'm deeply hurt.

1137
01:30:00,259 --> 01:30:02,119
At least our last
night will be fun.

1138
01:30:02,177 --> 01:30:04,287
Please don't do this, guys.

1139
01:30:05,097 --> 01:30:09,591
This is happening because we miss him.
And we're really hurting.

1140
01:30:10,894 --> 01:30:12,968
That's a crock of shit!

1141
01:30:13,021 --> 01:30:16,341
We're afraid just the
opposite is true.

1142
01:30:16,400 --> 01:30:18,676
Alex died for most of
us a long time ago.

1143
01:30:19,987 --> 01:30:22,393
I think you're a crock of shit.

1144
01:30:22,823 --> 01:30:24,850
Don't speak for me or anybody else.

1145
01:30:24,908 --> 01:30:27,267
You hate your life.
That's your problem.

1146
01:30:27,453 --> 01:30:29,610
- Don't tell us how we feel, okay?
- That's it.

1147
01:30:29,663 --> 01:30:32,947
That's all I'm saying. If I
hate my life, it's my problem.

1148
01:30:34,084 --> 01:30:38,234
Too bad you weren't around to
comfort Alex as compassionately.

1149
01:30:40,090 --> 01:30:42,413
We go back a long way.

1150
01:30:42,509 --> 01:30:45,117
I won't piss that away because
you're higher than a kite.

1151
01:30:45,179 --> 01:30:48,048
A long time ago we knew each
other for a short period.

1152
01:30:48,098 --> 01:30:51,169
You don't know anything about me.

1153
01:30:51,894 --> 01:30:54,585
It was easy then. No one had
a cushier berth than we did.

1154
01:30:54,646 --> 01:30:56,673
It's not surprising our
friendship could survive that.

1155
01:30:56,732 --> 01:30:59,505
It's only here in the
world that it gets tough.

1156
01:31:00,986 --> 01:31:02,597
I don't care what you say.

1157
01:31:04,073 --> 01:31:06,977
I know I loved you and
everybody else here.

1158
01:31:07,034 --> 01:31:09,939
And I'll go on believing
that till I kick.

1159
01:31:15,000 --> 01:31:18,201
What's wrong with you?
What's happened to you?

1160
01:31:35,104 --> 01:31:36,418
Wait!

1161
01:31:41,944 --> 01:31:45,762
I believe you can help
other people. I really do.

1162
01:31:45,823 --> 01:31:47,137
Sorry about that.

1163
01:31:47,241 --> 01:31:48,721
I do too.

1164
01:31:49,159 --> 01:31:52,146
Not that you can save
them, probably not.

1165
01:31:52,246 --> 01:31:54,355
But you can do what you can do.

1166
01:31:54,415 --> 01:31:56,441
That's how I feel.

1167
01:31:58,961 --> 01:32:01,866
So lay into me now.
Really let me have it.

1168
01:32:01,922 --> 01:32:04,993
I was just trying to keep
the conversation lively.

1169
01:32:06,969 --> 01:32:10,585
So you'll continue to
love me no matter what?

1170
01:32:10,639 --> 01:32:12,499
Just don't cross me.

1171
01:32:14,059 --> 01:32:16,252
Could you help me
in here for a sec?

1172
01:32:21,525 --> 01:32:24,809
Well, I think I've had enough.

1173
01:32:54,433 --> 01:32:56,922
I love you very much.

1174
01:33:00,355 --> 01:33:01,931
I'm yours.

1175
01:33:02,524 --> 01:33:05,262
I want you to do something for me.

1176
01:33:05,903 --> 01:33:07,182
Anything.

1177
01:33:07,738 --> 01:33:10,061
I'd marry you, if you want.

1178
01:33:10,157 --> 01:33:11,816
No, wait. I did that.

1179
01:33:12,242 --> 01:33:13,985
Yes, you did.

1180
01:33:14,036 --> 01:33:15,695
Thank God.

1181
01:33:17,915 --> 01:33:19,657
It's about Meg.

1182
01:33:46,151 --> 01:33:47,632
Where to?

1183
01:33:51,740 --> 01:33:53,849
You know, I don't do anything.

1184
01:34:04,294 --> 01:34:05,490
It's me.

1185
01:34:05,546 --> 01:34:08,034
Come on in. Nobody else will.

1186
01:35:07,024 --> 01:35:10,178
This bed has always been
lucky for Sarah and me.

1187
01:35:13,489 --> 01:35:16,014
I got to try and relax.

1188
01:35:19,036 --> 01:35:21,442
I think I just forgot how to do it.

1189
01:35:39,807 --> 01:35:41,038
What, what?

1190
01:35:41,100 --> 01:35:43,838
It's not going to come out right.

1191
01:35:43,977 --> 01:35:45,257
Try me.

1192
01:35:49,441 --> 01:35:53,556
I feel like I got a great
break on a used car.

1193
01:36:12,214 --> 01:36:13,908
I remember this.

1194
01:36:15,759 --> 01:36:18,035
I remember when he got this.

1195
01:37:09,855 --> 01:37:12,261
<i>I must tell you...</i>

1196
01:37:12,775 --> 01:37:16,011
<i>I'm picking up vibrations
here at the house.</i>

1197
01:37:16,111 --> 01:37:19,763
<i>I'm almost certain there's
sex going on around here.</i>

1198
01:37:21,450 --> 01:37:24,770
<i>Have I ever told you how
beautiful your eyes are?</i>

1199
01:37:28,332 --> 01:37:29,812
<i>My head.</i>

1200
01:37:33,712 --> 01:37:35,193
<i>Your feet.</i>

1201
01:37:37,091 --> 01:37:38,701
<i>Tell me about the club.</i>

1202
01:37:38,759 --> 01:37:41,248
<i>Fuck the club. I couldn't
deal with the hours.</i>

1203
01:37:41,303 --> 01:37:43,543
<i>It'd be nothing but aggravation.</i>

1204
01:37:43,847 --> 01:37:46,669
<i>Let's say it becomes successful.
I become a star.</i>

1205
01:37:46,767 --> 01:37:51,012
<i>People magazine sends a
nasty schmuck like me...</i>

1206
01:37:51,063 --> 01:37:52,805
<i>to do interviews. Big deal.</i>

1207
01:37:52,856 --> 01:37:55,630
<i>Nope. I'm going back to my novel.</i>

1208
01:37:56,151 --> 01:37:57,596
<i>I'll write about this weekend.</i>

1209
01:37:57,694 --> 01:38:00,017
<i>What were you going to
write about before?</i>

1210
01:38:01,490 --> 01:38:03,149
<i>Last weekend.</i>

1211
01:39:07,473 --> 01:39:09,879
If Richard and I bring
the boys to L.A...

1212
01:39:09,975 --> 01:39:13,211
maybe you could get
us in to see a studio.

1213
01:39:13,604 --> 01:39:15,179
Yeah, sure.

1214
01:39:15,272 --> 01:39:16,966
Absolutely.

1215
01:39:17,274 --> 01:39:18,849
No problem.

1216
01:39:19,777 --> 01:39:21,139
Good.

1217
01:39:22,571 --> 01:39:24,479
Richard would like that.

1218
01:39:36,543 --> 01:39:38,403
I'm the worst about writing.

1219
01:39:38,462 --> 01:39:42,197
But I promise I will, from
now on, answer your letters.

1220
01:39:42,257 --> 01:39:44,913
- Great.
- Good morning, youngsters.

1221
01:39:45,844 --> 01:39:49,081
So how did everybody
sleep last night?

1222
01:39:49,139 --> 01:39:51,379
Did anybody sleep last night?

1223
01:39:53,352 --> 01:39:55,924
I know I did. All
alone in my airplane.

1224
01:39:55,979 --> 01:39:59,216
No co-pilot. I slept like a baby.
Even wet the bed.

1225
01:39:59,525 --> 01:40:01,598
Drink your coffee, Michael.

1226
01:40:03,570 --> 01:40:06,724
I'll come see you whether
you like it or not.

1227
01:40:07,658 --> 01:40:09,138
Well, good morning.

1228
01:40:10,619 --> 01:40:12,064
Good morning.

1229
01:40:13,163 --> 01:40:14,739
How you doing?

1230
01:40:15,874 --> 01:40:18,233
Don't have to be in
such a good mood.

1231
01:40:21,505 --> 01:40:24,326
Look what I found in Alex's papers.

1232
01:40:26,927 --> 01:40:29,618
I will be in Detroit
sometime on this deal...

1233
01:40:29,722 --> 01:40:31,998
and I'm just dying
to meet your boys.

1234
01:40:32,057 --> 01:40:33,288
I'd love it.

1235
01:40:33,392 --> 01:40:36,047
- You're all welcome in New York.
- Great!

1236
01:40:36,103 --> 01:40:38,876
Not in my apartment, you understand.
But in the city.

1237
01:40:38,939 --> 01:40:42,057
I'll accompany you anywhere,
even to Elaine's.

1238
01:40:42,151 --> 01:40:43,549
Thought Elaine's was dead.

1239
01:40:43,610 --> 01:40:46,218
That's why I can get you guys in.

1240
01:40:46,947 --> 01:40:48,096
What's that?

1241
01:40:48,157 --> 01:40:51,975
The column I wrote about Alex when
he turned down the fellowship.

1242
01:40:53,203 --> 01:40:55,562
This is not bad. Good, clean style.

1243
01:40:55,622 --> 01:40:59,322
Lean, economical, the right touch
of ideological fanaticism.

1244
01:40:59,543 --> 01:41:02,151
I remember Alex was
angry about that.

1245
01:41:02,254 --> 01:41:03,948
What do you mean?
I made him famous.

1246
01:41:04,048 --> 01:41:05,991
Think he saved it
because he hated it?

1247
01:41:06,050 --> 01:41:08,207
He also saved his induction notice.

1248
01:41:09,470 --> 01:41:11,662
I'm collecting addresses.
Do you have one?

1249
01:41:11,722 --> 01:41:14,164
Or should I copy down
your license plate?

1250
01:41:16,685 --> 01:41:19,174
You can reach Nick
here for a while.

1251
01:41:19,271 --> 01:41:24,180
Nick and Chloe will stay here and
do some work at the old house.

1252
01:41:36,830 --> 01:41:40,031
I guess there's a certain
symmetry to that.

1253
01:41:42,920 --> 01:41:46,074
What's the flight schedule here?
Is there any way...

1254
01:41:46,173 --> 01:41:48,330
to coordinate the
airport transport?

1255
01:41:48,384 --> 01:41:49,912
I'll be glad to drive somebody.

1256
01:41:50,010 --> 01:41:52,748
Great, if we can take Harold's car.

1257
01:41:53,055 --> 01:41:54,417
Get Harold to drive it.

1258
01:41:54,473 --> 01:41:56,381
You're no fun.

1259
01:41:56,725 --> 01:42:00,045
That won't be necessary.
We took a secret vote.

1260
01:42:00,145 --> 01:42:02,304
We're not leaving.
We're never leaving.
